      • order

        private boolean order
        Flags whether this structure definition is ordered. An order structure definition means that processes in it are not isomorphic, in other words, structure<i1, i2, ..> is not equivalent to structure<i2, i1, ..>. If the structure is not ordered, then the indices will be always re-arranged such that the smaller index (according to the natural ordering of strings in java) will be first, Which is useful in order to avoid duplication. If the structure is not ordered, then the indices will not be re-arranged, and the same structure with different arrangement of indices will not be considered as a duplicate.

    • Constructor Detail

      • StructureTemplate

        public StructureTemplate(java.lang.String name,
                         java.lang.String[] indices,
                         java.lang.String definition,
                         boolean order)
        Creates a new template for a structure.
        Parameters:
        name - the base name of the template.
        indices - the symbolic indices the structure takes (in order of replacement).
        definition - the definition of the structure.
        order - if true, then the template represents an a-symmetric structure (i.e. changing the process indices order resulting in a different structure), false otherwise.

      • update

        public void update(java.lang.String[] indices,
                   java.lang.String definition,
                   boolean order)
        Updates the template to the given template. Useful for when the template name is used again with a new define statement. Preserves the counter to preserve unique names for generated structures.
        Parameters:
        indices - the symbolic indices the structure takes (in order of replacement).
        definition - the definition of the structure.
        order - if true, then the template represents an a-symmetric structure (i.e. changing the process indices order resulting in a different structure), false otherwise.

      • instantiate

        public Structure instantiate(java.lang.String[] replacements)
                      throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Instantiate a new structure from this template. The indices that were provided in the template definition will be replaced by the given replacements (in order).
        Parameters:
        replacements - the indices to use as replacements.
        Returns:
        the new structure definition, null if two indices (or more) were equal.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the replacements count does not match the defined indices count.
